leads.lead_text: Sepals more than 15 mm long, each tapered to a fine long point; leaf bluntly toothed (sometimes minutely)
Sepals less than 15 mm long, terminating in a shorter point; never thread-like; leaf not toothed
Petals spreading, not reflexed towards the ovary; dorsal sepal hooded closely over column
Petals reflexed towards the ovary; dorsal sepal not hooded closely over column
Dorsal sepal 6–8 mm long, usually somewhat warty; labellum all or mostly reddish-purple; north-east Victoria
Dorsal sepal 9–12 mm long, smooth or very nearly so; labellum wholly green or green and maroon; near-coastal far east Victoria
Labellum 6–7 mm long, ovate-cordate, base of lamina truncate to cordate
Labellum 3–5 mm long, oblong-ovate to ovate-lanceolate, base of lamina broadly wedge-shaped or squarish with rounded corners
